The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Russian connection for Shyam Telelink

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Sept. 26: Russian private sector consumer services company AFK Systema has acquired a 10 per cent stake in the Shyam Telecom group firm Shyam Telelink, which provides basic telecom services in Rajasthan.

 AFK Systemas key asset is Russias largest mobile services provider Mobile TeleSystems. It also has business ventures in insurance, media, banking and real estate.

 AFK Systema plans to increase its stake to 51 per cent, subject to approval from the Foreign Investment Promotion Board. 

 The company, in the long run, plans to take the stake to 74 per cent, as is allowed under the FDI policy. 

 On the Bombay Stock Exchange, Shyam Telecoms shares surged nearly 20 per cent today to Rs 96.45. 

 Shyam Telelinks, which provides services under the brands Rainbow and Citymobile in Rajasthan, has applied for licences to start operations in 21 circles.

 The deal valuation is not available yet, but sources said the deal put a good value to Shyam Telelinks subscriber base in Rajasthan. Company officials were not available for comments.

 A formal announcement is imminent, sources added.

 Shyam Telelink runs a state-wide fixed-line and wireless terminal access network using CDMA technology and has 2,57,108 subscribers as of the end of August. 




